The plugin will take an element containing some other elements and will generate a menu for sliding between them.


HTML structure:

<div id="container">
	<div>slide 1</div>
	<div>slide 2</div>
	<div>slide 2</div>
</div>

or

<ul id="container">
	<li>slide 1</li>
	<li>slide 2</li>
	<li>slide 2</li>
</ul>

javascript:

$('#container').wkslider();

parameters:

- slideElement		: the slide element tagName
- menuClass			: class attached to the generated menu container [defalut: 'slider_menu']
- activate			: class attached to the active menu's selector [default: 'active']
- selector 			:
	-- 'number' for numerical menu i.e. (1,2,3,..,n)
	-- 'character' for alphabetical menu i.e. (a,b,c,..)
	-- any other string will be used as selector, default is 'o' which will produce (o,o,o,o,..)
- autoplay			: makes plugin slides on his own [default: false]
- time				: interval of time between a slide and the next during autoplay [default: 3000]


examples of usage: http://jsfiddle.net/KCAZF/5/